<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A city school bus with 23 children on board collided with a car in City Heights 
Wednesday afternoon, firefighters said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car, Caryn Fries, 25, of El Centro was taken to Villa View 
hospital with minor head injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Although a few children, ages 12 to 14, complained of minor injuries, none was 
hospitalized, firefighter Larry Stewart said. 
</P>
<P>
Bus driver Dora Vidrio escaped injury in the accident, which occurred about 
3:30 p.m. at Violet Street and Pepper Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol is investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, School bus driver Dora Vidrio gives a California Highway Patrol officer 
her account of traffic accident Wednesday. KENNETH K. LAM / Los Angeles Times 
