<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The president of Newsweek Inc., Christopher M. Little, has resigned to become 
president of Cowles Magazines Inc., which publishes history magazines and 
books. Little, 47, had been president of Newsweek for the past 2 1/2 years. He 
said he is taking the new job because of his interest in history and the chance 
to live closer to his Virginia farm. His resignation is effective March 1. 
Washington Post Co., parent of Newsweek, named no replacement for Little. 
</P>
