<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USAir Group's 1988 profit was off 15% to $165 million. Operating revenue rose 
to $5.7 billion, up 90%. The Washington-based operator of USAir, Piedmont 
Aviation and four commuter airlines credited the results to one-time expenses 
related to merging Pacific Southwest Airlines with USAir last April and 
establishment of a $33-million reserve to reduce the company's investment in 
its BAC 1-11 aircraft and related spares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
