<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEEF BUNDLES GIVE MOM THE NIGHT OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This idea for Beef Bundles is an ideal way to give Mom the night off. Let the 
children help prepare the packets, then just whisk the packets into the oven. 
</P>
<P>
Cut 1 pound top round steak into 4 serving-size portions. Dust each with 
mixture of 2 tablespoons flour combined with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon 
thyme and dash black pepper and dash paprika. Place each portion in center of 
12-inch, double-thick square of heavy-duty foil. Combine 1 cup sliced carrots, 
1 cup sliced zucchini and 1/4 cup sliced green onions and place even amounts of 
vegetable mixture in meat packets. Fold foil over and seal edges tightly. Roast 
at 325 degrees about 1 hour or until steak is tender. 
</P>
</TEXT>
