<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECONSIDER SALE OF PASADENA YMCA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am writing to you as an outraged member of the Pasadena YMCA. I cannot 
believe that the members were not allowed to be included in the decision to 
sell the building. Consideration for the members was obviously not a factor in 
the board's decision to sell the building. 
</P>
<P>
I, along with many other members, do not have an alternative fitness center 
that is within a reasonable distance and price. I work out primarily on my 
lunch hour, so I cannot drive to other YMCAs in other cities within my time 
constraints. 
</P>
<P>
It is my opinion that the board should represent the wishes of its members and 
be accountable to them. I truly feel that the present board is not reflecting 
the best interest of its membership and should be replaced, and the decision to 
sell abandoned so that other alternatives and arrangements can be made. 
</P>
<P>
STEVEN F. BEHRENS 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 
</P>
<P>
The San Gabriel Valley section of The Times welcomes all viewpoints from 
readers about issues in the San Gabriel Valley. Letters should be as brief as 
possible and are subject to condensation. They must include signature, valid 
mailing address and telephone number, if any. Pseudonyms and initials will not 
be used. Send letters to: San Gabriel Valley Editor, Los Angeles Times, 1333 
Mayflower Ave., Suite 200, Monrovia 91016. 
</P>
