<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEDOM FROM RELIGION OR BULLYING THE PUBLIC? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am greatly concerned about "Freedom From Religion" groups twisting the truth 
and bullying their way into communities such as ours. How dare they claim, with 
arrogance, that certain traditions in this great country of ours are abuses of 
the laws. 
</P>
<P>
Thanksgiving is a longstanding tradition in our country and, like it or not, so 
is religion. The entire foundation of this country is based on freedom to 
develop as the general consensus sees fit, not as a few disgruntled people 
demand. 
</P>
<P>
The use of churches as polling places does not offend the general public. What 
do they think we do, corrupt the minds of the voters? 
</P>
<P>
Separation of church and state refers to protecting us from a prescribed state 
religion, or any religious beliefs, not the forcing of religion from society, 
as they would insist. 
</P>
<P>
JERRY BLAUER 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
