<HEADLINE>
<P>
16 DRUG TRAFFICKERS EXECUTED IN IRAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixteen drug smugglers were hanged in Iran on Wednesday after a major 
anti-narcotics crackdown, Tehran Radio reported. 
</P>
<P>
Ten key members of the gang were hanged in Tehran, two smugglers were executed 
in neighboring Varamin and four in western Bakhtaran province, according to the 
broadcast, monitored in Nicosia. 
</P>
<P>
These deaths raised to 89 the number of drug smugglers executed since the 
crackdown started Jan. 16. More than 1,000 people have been arrested in the 
same period in what Iranian newspapers describe as "the biggest crackdown on 
drug smuggling in Iranian history." 
</P>
<P>
A new narcotics law, which went into effect Saturday, carries the death penalty 
for possession of just over an ounce of heroin and for 11 pounds of opium or 
hashish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
