METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
IRWINDALE TO GIVE CONSULTANT BACK PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Irwindale City Council has approved the payment of $53,400 to public 
relations consultant Xavier Hermosillo to settle his claim for back wages. 
</P>
<P>
Hermosillo was hired by City Manager Charles Martin in 1987 to primarily handle 
questions from the media concerning the possible move of the Los Angeles 
Raiders to Irwindale. 
</P>
<P>
Although he was paid $8,500 a month as a consultant, Hermosillo said Irwindale 
owed him additional money for nearly 500 hours of public relations work 
unconnected with the Raiders deal. 
</P>
<P>
Hermosillo billed the city for the wages shortly after he resigned from the 
consulting job last June. 
</P>
