<P>
DRUNK DRIVER GETS 14 MONTHS IN JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Pomona man pleaded guilty Wednesday to a drunk-driving charge for the 11th 
time in the past eight years and was sentenced to 14 months in County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
William R. Hilbert, 43, also had his driver's license revoked for four years 
and was placed on probation for five years by Municipal Court Commissioner 
Ronald Grey. 
</P>
<P>
Hilbert, an unemployed former firefighter, was sentenced after pleading guilty 
to driving under the influence of alcohol, driving with a blood-alcohol content 
above the legal limit of 0.10% and driving with a revoked license, all 
misdemeanors. 
</P>
<P>
In December, Hilbert was ordered held in lieu of $250,000 bail after a 
prosecutor said his blood-alcohol level had often been three times the legal 
limit, adding, "I cannot believe this guy hasn't killed someone." 
</P>
</TEXT>
