<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A district judge in Dunn, N.C., threw the book at a drunken driver with a 
21-page arrest record, sentencing him to seven years in prison and raising his 
bond to $100,000 after his 33rd drunken-driving conviction. Otis Wadford, 52, 
who pleaded guilty to the charge, was also fined $4,000 by Judge Sam 
Stephenson, who said he was appalled by the Raleigh man's record. In addition 
to his 33 drunken-driving convictions, Wadford's 21-page record showed he had 
been convicted 22 times of driving after his license had been revoked. 
</P>
