<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Big Rig Was Just Too Tall Truck driver Tom Inglis is brought up short on 
the San Diego Freeway at a ramp under construction to link John Wayne Airport 
with MacArthur Boulevard. The ramp was just a little too low for Inglis' cargo, 
which was being driven south on the freeway Wednesday morning. The bulldozer he 
was hauling stood 15 feet, 11 inches above the pavement, but the clearance was 
only 15 feet, 7 1/2 inches. The bulldozer had to be unloaded on one side of the 
ramp, then reloaded on the other side after the truck was driven through. The 
incident caused a SigAlert and stopped southbound traffic for nearly 2 hours. 
DON KELSEN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
