<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
MEETING SCHEDULED ON 1990 CENSUS BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents and community leaders are invited to attend a special presentation 
Tuesday on the city's 1990 Census Outreach Project to highlight the importance 
and benefits of participating in the 1990 Census. 
</P>
<P>
According to a statement released by the city, a major effort will be made next 
year to reach Latino, Vietnamese, Cambodian, Laotian and other ethnic 
populations within Santa Ana because their numbers have not been accurately 
represented in previous census counts. These groups, the statement said, have 
been difficult to reach because of language and cultural barriers. 
</P>
<P>
Guest speaker at the event, co-hosted by the city and Voces Unidas, a Latino 
organization, will be John E. Reeder Jr., a representative of the U.S. 
Department of Commerce. The presentation will be at 1 p.m. at the Corbin 
Community Center, 2215 W. McFadden Ave. 
</P>
<P>
For more information or to reserve seating, contact Martha Gallegos, Census 
outreach supervisor, at (714) 647-6557. Admission and parking are free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
