SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WOMEN'S GOLF 
</P>
<P>
With a 54-hole total of 238, U.S. International's Allison Shapcott finished 
ninth in the Yamaha-USC Invitational on the 6,157-yard par-72 course at the 
Oakmont Country Club in Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State's Karen Enberg finished 17th with a 243 and Tupito Walker 
(USIU) and Wendy Kaupp (SDSU) finished tied for 23rd. 
</P>
<P>
In the team competition, USIU was eighth, SDSU ninth. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego defeated UC Santa Barbara, 5-1, to run its record 
to 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
USD defeated Pepperdine Tuesday. 
