IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LANCIAS SWEEP MONTE CARLO RALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTE CARLO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
World champion Massimo Biasion of Italy won the 57th Monte Carlo Rally, leading 
a sweep today of the first three places by Lancia Integrales. 
</P>
<P>
Biasion, who took the lead last Sunday, was timed at seven hours, 13 minutes, 
27 seconds for the event. He had a lead of 6:27 over teammate Didier Auriol of 
France. In third place was Bruno Saby of Italy, 7:41 behind. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first 1-2-3 sweep for Lancia in the Monte Carlo Rally since 1976 
when Sandro Munari, Bjorn Waldegard and Bernard Darniche took the top three 
spots. 
</P>
<P>
Biasion also won the Monte Carlo Rally two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
